<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-15T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-15T08:00:00-05:00" n="735" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d735">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">353q116/10: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-15T13:00:00+00:00">January 15, 1930—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. Department’s telegraphic instructions of January 14, 2 p.m. Decree
                            objected to by foreign missions has been indefinitely suspended; see
                            Legation’s mail despatches December 30 and January 2, respectively.<note n="26" xml:id="d735fn26">Neither printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi></signed></closer>
